register.description: CPU Status Register provides information about the progress of the CPU execution

This bit is set to '1' when in Debug mode, an EndOfPgm instruction or the last instruction of ProgramBuffer has been reached.
This bit is set to '1' when a StopSeq() command has been issued and the iME is in Halted state.

This bit is set to '1' when the last instruction of the Program Buffer is reached, and no EndPgm() or LoadInstBuf() instruction have been detected in the program buffer.This bit is cleared by a StartSeq() command.
This bit is set to '1' when a unknown opcode is decoded from the main program.This bit is cleared by StartSeq() command when in INITIALIZED state, or by a Stop() command.

This bit is set to '1' when attempting to write to an internal register through an OCP Write, while in EXECUTING state.This bit is cleared by StartSeq() command when in INITIALIZED state, or by a Stop() command.
Execution States:00 = Initialized,10 = Executing,01 = Halted,11 = Completed.
